have a cingular lg if that helps any... thanks to all\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(58048,312,'pam','pppppppppppam@yahoo.com','','58.69.229.90','2006-05-23 08:55:24','2006-05-23 15:55:24','its really this:\n16g1 16- 16g1 16- 16#a1 16g1\ntempo: 125\n\nits only for nokia only.\ntry to compose it then compare it to the original. its the same.\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(58050,312,'Adie','','','161.16.0.112','2006-06-11 23:49:59','2006-06-12 06:49:59','Hi, I\'m looking for the Kimmunicator beeps for a Siemans....thanks\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(58051,312,'Max','UT_Andrew@arcor.de','','141.30.228.102','2006-06-20 09:24:57','2006-06-20 16:24:57','Somebody who has got the mid-File of the Kimmunicator can send me, please. I want to put it to a Siemens A55\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(59553,314,'axim','kukuruza11@ua.fm','http://www.popularpdareview.com/','194.44.186.64','2006-01-11 01:44:00','2006-01-11 08:44:00','It\'s nice to know that people from around the world are all working toward easier economical gadgets and computers, I think google should look at that to join their 100$ computer.\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(60872,321,'Tapwave Zodiac','','http://portagame.com/tapwave_zodiac.php/2004/05/24/p132-Blogging_on_Tapwave_s_Zodiac','69.93.191.202','2004-05-24 16:12:46','2004-05-24 23:12:46','<strong>Blogging on Tapwave\'s Zodiac</strong>\n\nLonnie at Tribblescape has found another reason to purchase the Tapwave Zodiac...Blogging. He may just have the first documented case of blogging using Moveable Type\'s web interface on Zodiac\'s included web browser. It all seemed to work fine, at the ...\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(61241,322,'matt','Orb2069@yahoo.com','','68.251.121.30','2005-01-29 17:23:07','2005-01-30 00:23:07','The Treo line answer to your wife\'s problem is to include a speakerphone.  It\'s not a great solution, but it IS servicable in less-noisy enviroments.\n\nI think the 650 provides improvements on most of what you\'re mentioning -  IMO, the biggest dissapointment of PDA/Celphones is that you really can\'t try them out in the store very easily.\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(61242,322,'Cliff','teddybear65@hotmail.com','','207.236.90.177','2005-05-20 07:44:22','2005-05-20 14:44:22','U all suck ook\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(61243,322,'Lonnon','lonnon.foster@gmail.com','http://blog.nyerm.com','131.107.0.88','2005-05-20 10:07:04','2005-05-20 17:07:04','Hooray for the Internet, bastion of intelligent discourse. Thank you, Cliff, for your verbose and thoughtful commentary.\r\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(62212,326,'Calvin','mew905@hotmail.com','','206.163.255.76','2004-11-04 14:42:45','2004-11-04 21:42:45','I completely agree with the flashlight thing.  Also, its fun hitting the enemies with the flashlight.  One of my friends is still running through the second level, he\'s afraid to do anything.  I love the darkness effect, it keeps you on your toes, and if you have speakers with alot of bass, hehe, have fun, you can literally feel the big enemies comin. There are alot of dramatic scenes in Doom 3, and as far as I know, the \"guardian\" is the toughest enemy in the game.  But, thats just my opinion.  Have fun little dudes :D\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(62858,328,'malcolm taylor','malcolm.taylor@wanadoo.fr','','83.138.136.91','2005-07-09 08:16:55','2005-07-09 15:16:55','Hello. I\'m seeking a font for an existing 1929 cover design.\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(62859,328,'collision detection','','http://www.collisiondetection.net/mt/archives/001003.html','209.68.1.153','2004-10-17 23:00:44','2004-10-18 06:00:44','<strong>I can name that font in six notes</strong>\n\nHere\'s a cool site: Identifont, an online tool for helping you find a font you can sort of half-imagine but don\'t know the name for. If you have an idea of a font you\'re trying to locate, Identifont will throw a bunch of questions at you -- i.e. \"Does...\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64389,335,'Tom F.','frauen1@gmail.com','','67.84.56.130','2005-06-24 06:47:29','2005-06-24 13:47:29','You know the kicker was that according to Danica Parker he called he on the phone and both praised her and reiterated the comment above.  She was very confused by this and is now even more upset.\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64390,336,'AWA','squap@one.lv','','195.2.101.85','2005-07-09 03:01:43','2005-07-09 10:01:43','real\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64391,336,'meltin','jatone6@hotmail.com','','62.1.226.23','2005-10-12 07:07:23','2005-10-12 14:07:23','addons need for wow\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64392,336,'Coogrrr','coogrrr25@hotmail.com','http://n/a','24.20.209.94','2006-01-04 07:27:42','2006-01-04 14:27:42','can you send me your backed up lua file I lost mine the same way hence me landing here looking for a way to never let it happen again\n\nThank you in advance!\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64393,336,'todd','toddheartcheese@hotmail.com','','69.91.54.120','2006-05-25 13:19:18','2006-05-25 20:19:18','yea...\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64394,338,'c0d3monk33','c0d3monk33@fastmail.fm','http://www.tabletop-terrain.com/','219.89.172.44','2005-10-31 15:14:31','2005-10-31 22:14:31','Wow. I can\'t believe people are still using this humble app I wrote years ago :). I\'m the original author...I still work in the mobile space...and I\'m actually thinking of re-writing Timesheet for J2ME capable mobile phones rather than the rapidly expiring PalmOS platform...\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64395,338,'effgee','eff@ozemail.com.au','','203.214.103.202','2006-01-22 17:11:33','2006-01-23 00:11:33','I have been specifically searching for a j2me replacement for timesheet 1.5.3, so the sooner the better !\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64396,354,'Frode Hegland','frode@hyperwords.net','http://www.hyperwords.net','65.172.237.112','2006-03-07 20:17:04','2006-03-08 03:17:04','This is the problem we are having with trying to develop a command-key \'language\' for Hyperwords.\n\n(Hyperwords is a Firefox Extension that makes all the words on the web interactive, for searches, references, emailing, blogging, tagging, translations and more. If you\'d like to try it, it\'s available for download (for free) from <a href=\"http://www.hyperwords.net\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.hyperwords.net</a> )\n\nMost of the time we are using the first letter as the keyboard shortcut, so that you can do \'rw\' for \'Reference: Wikipedia\' but it\'s not always that simple and there are cases where we are going for language like grammar \'Email; immediately\' but this doesn\'t always make sense, for example with categories under \'Map\'.\n\nIt\'s not hard designing shortcuts without quirks!\n',0,'1','','',0,0),(64604,483,'Johannes','johannes@donya.se','','41.204.128.101','2009-05-15 11:09:15','2009-05-15 18:09:15','Check out the resource_hacks plugin:\r\n\r\n\"resource_hacks is a plugin that extends edge Rails new restful routes implementation. While the current opinion of the core team is that we should only use member resources with a numeric id, resource_hacks allows Rails to support arbitrary an arbitrary member path.\"\r\n\r\nhttp://archive.jvoorhis.com/articles/2006/08/01/announcing-resource_hacks\r\n\r\nCheers!',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; sv-SE; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)','',0,0),(64613,567,'John','johnogara@gmail.com','','89.101.22.222','2009-11-04 14:40:15','2009-11-04 21:40:15','Cheers for the advise on this, I ran into an additional problem about half way through the mysql build, I got the error\r\nerror: `my_thread_var\' undeclared (first use in this function)\r\nturns out its a newly found bug, luckily there\'s a patch available here\r\nhttp://lists.mysql.com/commits/86246',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-GB; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4','',0,0),(64612,378,'Erica80','erica80@gawab.com','http://www.soundtaxi.org','77.91.130.42','2009-09-14 05:26:30','2009-09-14 12:26:30','sdfgsdfgsdfgsdfg\r\ndfgh\r\ndfgh\r\ndf\r\nghd\r\nfgh\r\ndf\r\nghdf\r\nh',0,'spam','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.0)','',0,0);
