upload a bunch of notes from the now-defunct \"Stikkit\":http://stikkit.com to my account on \"Helipad\":http://pad.helicoid.net, I wrote a Ruby wrapper for Helipad\'s XML-over-HTTP API. The interface takes care of all the XML magic, letting you concentrate on the fun stuff: playing with your documents on Helipad.\n\n<pre name=\"code\" class=\"ruby:nocontrols:nogutter\">\n  hp = Helipad.new(\"lonnon@example.com\",\n                   \"password\")\n  source = File.read(\"cake_recipe.txt\")\n  response = hp.create(:title  => \"Cake\",\n                       :tags   => \"recipe\",\n                       :source => source)\n  puts \"Recipe saved\" if response.saved?\n</pre>\n\nThe Helipad Ruby interface can be installed through rubygems:\n\nbq. <code>gem install Helipad --remote</code>\n\nDocumentation is available here:\n\n* \"Helipad Ruby interface documentation\":http://nyerm.com/helipad/docs\n\nIf you\'re interested in the source code and current state of development, you can find the Helipad Ruby interface over on RubyForge:\n\n* \"Helipad Ruby interface on RubyForge\":http://rubyforge.org/projects/helipad/','Helipad Ruby interface',0,'','publish','open','open','','helipad-ruby-interface','','','2009-03-06 04:53:53','2009-03-06 11:53:53','',0,'http://blog.nyerm.com/?p=451',0,'post','',0),(452,2,'2009-01-08 13:15:04','2009-01-08 20:15:04','Spurred by my need to upload a bunch of notes from the now-defunct \"Stikkit\":http://stikkit.com to my account on \"Helipad\":http://pad.helicoid.net, I wrote a Ruby wrapper for Helipad\'s XML-over-HTTP API.\n\nThe Helipad Ruby interface can be installed through rubygems:\n\nbq. <pre>gem ','Helipad Ruby interface',0,'','inherit','open','open','','451-revision','','','2009-01-08 13:15:04','2009-01-08 20:15:04','',451,'http://blog.nyerm.com/2009/01/08/451-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(453,2,'2009-01-08 13:15:25','2009-01-08 20:15:25','Spurred by my need to upload a bunch of notes from the now-defunct \"Stikkit\":http://stikkit.